excerpt: Seafront museum complex in former royal palace surrounded by parkland known for its many fountains.
detail_description: Peterhof, also known as Paleizencomplex in Peterhof, is a seafront museum complex located in a former royal palace surrounded by parkland. It is renowned for its numerous fountains and is a top destination for various activities such as water sports, boat rides, kiteboarding, and exploring gardens. The palace itself offers an intriguing glimpse into the lives of ancient inhabitants through its royal rooms and exclusive chandeliers.
name: Peterhof

excerpt: Majestic ensemble of fountains with unique, opulent architecture & golden statues.
detail_description: The Grand Cascade is a stunning ensemble of fountains located in the Peterhof estate, known for its opulent architecture and golden statues. Originally expanded by Empress Elizabeth, the park and fountains, including the magnificent Grand Cascade, continued to be improved throughout the 18th and 19th centuries. The main attractions within the well-thought-out Peterhof ensemble include the Grand Palace, Upper Gardens, Lower Gardens, and the Baroque-style Sea Channel.
name: Grand Cascade

detail_description: Imperial Yachts Museum is a small pavilion showcasing the yachting traditions of the Imperial family, initiated by Peter the Great. It's located near the Baltic Sea, offering views of Russian warships and serving as a summer residence for Russian monarchs. The museum features well-maintained displays of models, photographs, and accessories related to yachts and ships from different centuries. Despite its small size, visitors find it an interesting place to learn about maritime history.
name: Imperial Yachts Museum
address: Нижний парк, Петергоф, Saint Petersburg, Russia, 198510

excerpt: Riverside park of boreal forest & meadows, popular for walking, cycling & picnics.
detail_description: Nature Monument 'Park Sergievka' is a picturesque riverside park featuring a mix of boreal forest and meadows, making it a popular spot for leisurely walks, cycling, and picnics. The well-maintained paths offer opportunities to admire the beautiful landscape and abundant songbirds. The park also boasts several historical buildings within its territory, adding to its charm. Visitors can explore the gully with streams and ponds while being surrounded by impressive oak trees.
name: Nature Monument "Park Sergievka"

detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque park of Peterhof, the Benois Family Museum is a treasure trove dedicated to the illustrious legacy of the Benois family—a lineage that boasts an impressive array of architects, artists, sculptors, and musicians. Established in 1988, this museum showcases over 700 exhibits spread across 22 halls within the historic Maid of Honor buildings.
name: Benois Family Museum

detail_description: The Petrodvorets Watch Factory "Raketa" is located in the town of Peterhof, near St. Petersburg, known for its historical significance as the former residence of Russian Emperor Peter the Great and its stunning fountains. The factory offers free tours where visitors can learn about its long and eventful history, as well as the intricate process of watchmaking. Guests have praised the informative and friendly guides who provide clear explanations about the factory and its renowned brand.
name: Petrodvorets Watch Factory "Raketa"

detail_description: The Fountain-cracker "Water Road" is a captivating water feature located near the Monsplaisir Palace in the Lower Park area. It was created in 1721 and consists of an impressive display of 300 jets that form a stunning water arch. The fountain is equipped with body sensors that trigger its mesmerizing waterworks, adding an element of surprise for visitors.
name: Fountain-cracker "Water Road"

excerpt: Built for Peter the Great, this 1700s baroque retreat was inspired by a Parisian hunting lodge.
detail_description: The Marly Palace, a splendid example of baroque architecture from the 1700s, was commissioned by Peter the Great and is said to have been modeled after a hunting lodge in Paris. This elegant palace is situated in a picturesque park with bridges and footpaths that are perfect for leisurely strolls. The palace's beauty is further enhanced by its reflection on the glassy surface of the nearby lake.
name: Дворец Марли
address: Нижний парк, Петергоф, Saint Petersburg, Russia, 198510

excerpt: Elegant baroque palace built for Peter the Great in the 1700s, with an art & porcelain collection.
detail_description: Located in the Monplir district of Saint Petersburg, the museum contains an art and porcelain collection dating back to the 1700s. The interior is dreamy, with antique furniture and ornate plasterwork adorning its walls.
name: Monplezir

excerpt: Sprawling green space with Romanov summer residences, plus neo-Gothic towers, bridges & pavilions.
detail_description: Park Aleksandriya in Saint-Petersburg is a vast expanse of lush greenery adorned with summer residences from the Romanov era, as well as stunning neo-Gothic towers, bridges, and pavilions. This favorite park in the city is known for its immaculate upkeep and cleanliness, offering a serene escape without being overcrowded. The entrance fee for citizens is approximately 200 rubles while tourists pay around 300 rubles.
name: Park Aleksandriya
address: новый Петергоф вокзал, ул. Демьяна Бедного, St Petersburg, Russia, 198510

detail_description: The Samson Fountain is a central attraction within the Peterhof ensemble, which also includes the Grand Palace, Upper Gardens, Lower Gardens, and the Grand Cascade of fountains. This Baroque-style fountain is located in the Sea Channel, also known as the Channel of Samson. The fountain features a sculptural group called "Samson tearing the Lion's Mouth," commemorating the 25th anniversary of the Battle of Poltava.
name: Samson Fountain

excerpt: Storehouse & research library in an 18th-century palace complex, with a striking dome & gold spire.
detail_description: The Scientific Archives of the State Museum-Reserve "Peterhof" is a treasure trove nestled within an exquisite 18th-century palace complex, crowned by a stunning dome and golden spire. This remarkable site, established in the early 1800s, symbolizes Russia's burgeoning triumphs and has become one of St. Petersburg's most beloved attractions.
name: Scientific Archives of the State Museum-Reserve "Peterhof" |

detail_description: Nizhniy Park is a magical place where you can witness Russian Guards and future police officers being chased by dogs. The park is abundant with these beautiful animals, and their waste products are found everywhere. It's an interesting place to observe the Welcom law in action, especially when walking with children. The park features magnificent fountains that shoot water into the sky and ancient oak trees that add to its beauty.
name: Nizhniy Park

excerpt: Park with a small lake containing 2 islands & pavilions, landscaped gardens & lawned areas.
detail_description: Kolonistskiy Park is a recreational area featuring a petite reservoir harboring two islets and gazebos, well-kept gardens, and green expanses. This park offers visitors the chance to relax amidst its picturesque surroundings, comprising of a tiny body of water with two land masses nestled within it alongside covered structures for gathering or relaxation purposes. The meticulously maintained grounds encompass floral displays, manicured lawns, and open spaces where people can unwind and appreciate nature's beauty.
name: Kolonistskiy Park

detail_description: The beauty and grandeur of Goticheskiye Dvortsovyye Konyushni, an impressive historical site, leave a lasting impression. The magnificent architectural monuments, though sadly in a deplorable state, showcase the intricate craftsmanship of the past. This block-like structure holds within it beautiful buildings that once served as a sanatorium. With its closed Prada store and alluring surroundings, one can't help but be captivated by the charm and allure of this place.
name: Goticheskiye Dvortsovyye Konyushni

detail_description: Bridge Ruin, located in Alexandria Park, is a stunning attraction with a rich history. Constructed in 1828 by architect A. Menelas, the bridge was built using rough-hewn stone and limestone slabs, with birch trunk railings and decorative vases carved from Pudozh limestone. Originally intended to be part of a palace for A.D. Menshikov, the structure was repurposed into a bridge after plans changed.
name: Bridge Ruin

detail_description: The Fermerskiy Dvorets museum showcases an expansive and breathtaking garden that is truly extraordinary in size. This awe-inspiring location leaves visitors astonished with its magnificence. The museum boasts a vast array of attractions and features, leaving guests captivated and amazed by its offerings. It is an exceptional destination that cannot be missed, as it offers a remarkable experience for all who visit.
name: Fermerskiy Dvorets
address: парк Александрия 19 г. Санкт-Петербург, г. Петродворец, St Petersburg, Russia, 198510

detail_description: Samsonovskiy Kanal, also known as the Bolshoi Canal, is a picturesque waterway that runs through the Lower Park of Petrodvorets. It serves as the main compositional axis, connecting the Grand Cascade and the palace to the Gulf of Finland. The canal features 22 fountains and 2 bridges, offering stunning views of the palace. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely walk along its banks after exploring the castle and Samson's fountain.
name: Samsonovskiy Kanal

detail_description: The Pyramid Fountain is a remarkable and water-intensive attraction in the park, with up to 200 liters of water flowing per second. It symbolizes the enduring struggle for independence and cultural heritage. The fountain's architecture and powerful water flows create a magnificent and monumental sight, offering a magical experience. Despite being somewhat secluded from the main pathways, it is worth visiting for an exquisite and uncrowded experience. When activated, it transforms into a voluminous pyramid of water, showcasing its beauty.
name: Pyramid Fountain

detail_description: The Roman Fountains in Peterhof are a sight to behold, drawing inspiration from the fountains in St. Peter's Square in Rome. Originally crafted from wood with lead-lined bowls in 1739, they were later reconstructed under the guidance of F.B. Rastrelli in 1763, now resting on stone pedestals. To visit these stunning fountains, it's advisable to arrive early due to large crowds and long queues for tickets at the park and museums.
name: Roman fountains

detail_description: Zayachiy Remiz, a renowned historical site, has been widely known for its unique architecture and cultural significance. This prominent landmark stands as a testament to the past, showcasing remarkable craftsmanship and architectural brilliance. Although I haven't personally witnessed it, reports suggest that Zayachiy Remiz is generally in good condition. It serves as an emblem of the rich heritage associated with this region. Its distinct features captivate visitors, portraying a glimpse into the bygone era.
name: Zayachiy Remiz

detail_description: Bowl Fountains are a stunning feature located alongside the Big Cascade at Peterhof. These fountains boast powerful jets rising in a 25.5-meter pool, emphasizing their strength and competing with the Samson fountain. They create an impressive sight, especially when aligned with other nearby fountains like Chess Mount, Triton, and Adam and Eve.
name: Bowl Fountains

excerpt: 18th-century park with French-style landscaping, elegant buildings & fountains with gold statues.
detail_description: The Nizhny Park is an 18th-century green space that boasts of exquisite French-styled landscaping, remarkable constructions, and glistening fountains with golden sculptures. The park's layout is elegant and sophisticated, creating a serene environment ideal for relaxation and admiration of the natural beauty. Its architectural designs are awe-inspiring and reflect the rich history of the region while its ornamental features such as statues add to its grandeur.
name: Нижний парк

detail_description: The Monument to Peter I, the founder of Kronstadt, is a magnificent statue with intricate craftsmanship. It stands in the center of a serene and picturesque park adorned with numerous seating areas. This park is an ideal spot for a single visit, offering visitors the chance to admire the captivating details of the sculpture while enjoying moments of tranquility. Additionally, if one is fortunate enough, they may even have the opportunity to feed seagulls that casually roam near the nearby pier.
name: Monument to Peter I, the founder of Kronstadt

detail_description: Sektoral'nyye Prudy is a remarkably unique and stunning destination.
name: Sektoral'nyye Prudy

detail_description: Khram Svyatykh Pravednykh Simeona Bogopriimtsa I Anny Prorochitsy Goroda Sankt-Peterburga, also known as the Church of Saints Simon and Anna over frozen Fontanka River, is a historic church in Saint Petersburg.
name: Khram Svyatykh Pravednykh Simeona Bogopriimtsa I Anny Prorochitsy Goroda Sankt-Peterburga
Dom Starukhi-Protsentshchitsy
address: Griboyedov channel embankment, 104, St Petersburg, Russia, 190068

detail_description: The initial fountain situated at the garden's entrance is an impressive feature. It is known as the Mezheumnyy and has gained a reputation for its grandeur. This magnificent water feature welcomes visitors with its splendor as they enter the garden. Its location at the entrance adds to its significance, capturing attention right from the start. The Mezheumnyy fountain showcases exquisite design and craftsmanship, leaving a lasting impression on all who encounter it.
name: Mezheumnyy

detail_description: Fontan Solntse, also known as the Sun fountain, is a remarkable attraction in the Lower Park. The fountain features a rotating structure with water jets that imitate the sun's rays. It is adorned with gilded dolphins and has a 70-meter long pool with a bronze column in the center. The Menagere Garden surrounding the fountain reflects the tradition of housing rare birds and animals, adding to its allure.
name: Fontan Solntse

detail_description: Danaida Fountain in Peterhof is a serene and charming spot, often described as magnificent and cozy. The fountain exudes a tranquil atmosphere, with its golden hues adding to the allure of the place. It's a quiet and peaceful location that offers visitors a delightful experience.
name: Danaida
